    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This is what I am already doing for years. The discussion we had recently was an argue that t8n is not the tool to actually test clients since its implementation doesn't mimic client behavior as closely as in hive for instance.\n\nHowever I still see it as an access to evm and find it a good way to cross test different evm implementations\n\nThe t8ns I run on tests\ngeth\nNimbus \nEthereumjs \nEvmone\nBesu (too slow)\nPyt8n (too slow)\n\nThe pyspecs test I also integrate on test runner. \n\nSo as a summary: it doesn't matter which client generated the tests as long us all others agree on post state.\nThe current pyspecs already have support for other evms during filling. \n\nAnd it makes little sense to test fill on all clients(t8n) as they might pass  it during the generation but not on tommorows commit. We need a daily test run stats page to track down commits that break tests.\n\nHere are the daily t8n runs:\nhttp://retesteth.ethdevops.io ",
