    "body": "> This is only partly and temporarily useful. It would be much easier if I could run this process myself so I can use it directly in development.\r\n\r\nHi @chfast, I think it was Mario's intent to generate fixtures from multiple t8n binaries within one `fill` execution. The comparison would be made within the execution-spec-tests framework and the test case would fail if any of the generated test fixtures fail. In which case you could absolutely run this process locally or as part of your dev tooling. You would just have the other t8n tool(s) as dependencies. \r\n\r\nWould it be useful in that case?\r\n",
